      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is content autopilot software?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content autopilot software handles the entire content pipeline — keyword research, article writing, SEO optimization, and publishing — without manual intervention. You set it up, define your niche, and it produces and publishes content on schedule. Unlike writing tools that help you create content faster, autopilot software does the work for you.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best content autopilot software in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">It depends on your needs. For local businesses wanting blog + GBP + social, theStacc ($99/mo) covers the widest ground. For full-stack SEO automation, Search Atlas OTTO handles content + tech SEO + backlinks. For budget testing, SEO Bot starts at $19/mo with weekly articles.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can autopilot content actually rank on Google?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. AI-generated content regularly appears in top-10 results across competitive keywords. The key is quality and optimization. Tools with NLP scoring, proper internal linking, and topical authority planning perform best. Thin, keyword-stuffed output from bulk generators won't rank consistently.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How is content autopilot software different from AI writing tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">AI writing tools (Jasper, Writesonic, Frase) help you write faster — you still do keyword research, editing, formatting, and publishing. Content autopilot software handles the entire pipeline from keyword to published article without your involvement. The distinction is "helps you write" vs. "writes and publishes for you."</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does content autopilot software cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Prices range from $19/mo (SEO Bot, weekly articles) to $399+/mo (Search Atlas Pro). The sweet spot for most businesses is $99/mo, where theStacc, Outrank, and RankYak all deliver approximately 30 articles/month on full autopilot. By comparison, 30 articles from freelancers costs $2,400–$7,500/mo.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I still need to review content from autopilot tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
